Interesting course, learnt a lot. Very enjoyable tutorial. She is very passionate about the issues she teaches. However, she is unorganised and all over the place at times. Tries to cover way too much in one lecture. Was a bit judgemental, but she is helpful and approachable. Overall, good learning experience.

one of the best profs at u of t by far...im taking all of the classes she offers!

Pavlina is by far the best professor I've encountered within my University career here at UofT. I have taken courses on all three campuses and she is the most resonant, passionate and charismatic person I've met. I'm currently studying at erindale; however, I would commute to UTSC to be in one of her classes again. She is my inspiration.
